(419, 1, '2014-06-11 14:11:49', '2014-06-11 07:11:49', '<h2 style="margin-top: 0;">PERBANAS COUNCIL ( DIVISION )</h2>\r\n\r\n<div id="secretary-general" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>1. Secretary General</h3>\r\nKey Initiatives:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Support the Work Programs of all Divisions.</li>\r\n	<li>Organize regular Board Meetings and Plenary Meetings.</li>\r\n	<li>Activate KMPP.</li>\r\n	<li>Strengthen the Secretariat.</li>\r\n	<li>Drafting of the Secretariat Work Manual.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div id="treasurer" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>2. Treasurer</h3>\r\nKey Initiatives:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Consolidation of regional financial statements.</li>\r\n	<li>Make changes to the ‘chart of account’.</li>\r\n	<li>Evaluate YPP accounts.</li>\r\n	<li>Send audit reports to members.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div id="organization-division" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>3. Organization Division</h3>\r\nKey Initiatives:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Discourse to unify all regional banking activities into one organization which is Perbanas.</li>\r\n	<li>Regional Perbanas offices should be led by representatives of large banks / state-owned enterprises or CEOs of banks with head offices in regions.</li>\r\n	<li>“Synchronization of the Strategies and Activities of Central and Regional Perbanas (mandate of congress)” is perceived as ‘mirroring’ of Central Perbanas and is the key to the success of other programs.</li>\r\n	<li>Establishment of CEO Forum tailored to each group of banks.</li>\r\n	<li>Increase coordination between Banking organizations and Professions, involving IBI, Himbara, Asbanda, Asbisindo, and ASPI.</li>\r\n	<li>Coordination with Perbarindo can be done once a year to optimize linkage program.</li>\r\n	<li>Synchronization of events held in each banking association so as not to coincide.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div id="rnd-division" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>4. Research &amp; Development Division</h3>\r\nKey Initiatives:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Routine FGD (<em>hot issue</em>) once a month\r\na. Hearing with the House of Representatives\r\nb. FGD with Associations\r\nc. FGD on the Fee of Indonesian Financial Services Authority with Nonbank Institutions.\r\nd. FGD on Bank Conglomeration\r\ne. FGD on Banking Laws\r\nf. FGD on Outsourcing</li>\r\n	<li>Daily info (regulations / <em>hot issue</em>)</li>\r\n	<li>Assessment on Banking Efficiency</li>\r\n	<li>Financial Inclusion</li>\r\n	<li>Preparation of the banking industry in facing MEA</li>\r\n	<li>Socialization of policies</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div id="academic-and-human-resource-division" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>5. Academic &amp; Human Resource Division</h3>\r\nKey Initiatives:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Optimize the ‘link and match’ process with Perbanas Institute and STIE Perbanas Surabaya.</li>\r\n	<li>Actively provide input and propositions on National Health Insurance and provisions on outsourcing.</li>\r\n	<li>Availability of reliable human resource and technology system (in relation to the availability of human resources in the field of IT).</li>\r\n	<li>Support and actively participate in the banking and financial industry, specifically in addressing the ASEAN open market era in 2015 as well as encourage regulators in relation to the recruitment process of human resources in the banking and financial industry with a standardization and profession qualification which have been complied by Perbanas, IBI, and LSPP especially for foreign human resources in the upcoming open market era.</li>\r\n	<li>Involve and get involved in activities which are done in coordination with the regional Perbanas.</li>\r\n	<li>Strengthen the position of Perbanas as a working partner to regulators, specifically in drafting regulations related to human resources in the banking and financial industry, so as to present a good bargaining position for the association and the banking industry in general.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div id="foreign-affairs-division" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>6. Foreign Affairs Division</h3>\r\nKey Initiatives:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Establishment of “ASEAN One Integration” Committee</li>\r\n	<li>Gathering of information from various sources (Mr. Raden Pardede, Secretary General of ASEAN and BI) prior to the drafting of ‘Position Paper’ / ‘Working Paper’ which will be addressed at the ASEAN Banking Association annual event in Myanmar on 14-15 November 2013, Research and Development Division is hoped to assist in providing material related to the ASEAN Economic Community.</li>\r\n	<li>Based on the information gathered, a framework will be formulated which will be used as a reference for the drafting of ‘Position Paper’ / ‘Working Paper’ by Perbanas internal parties or to be handed over to another party (outsourcing). Several parties considered able to assist in the drafting of ‘Position Paper’ / ‘Working Paper’ is MM-UI, Mckinsey &amp; Company (Indonesia), Boston Consultant Group or other consultants.</li>\r\n	<li>Gathering of information from Perbanas members who have access to their holding banks in ASEAN countries, on regulations or initiatives which have or are being applied by banks in each ASEAN country, in preparation to face the ASEAN Economic Community 2020.</li>\r\n	<li>The Foreign Affairs Division will invite as many Perbanas members as possible to participate in the ABA Annual Meeting in Myanmar on 14-15 November 2013. Aside from participating in the Annual Meeting, participants will be able to explore the chances of building a business network in Myanmar.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div id="law-and-regulation-division" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>7. Law &amp; Regulations Division</h3>\r\nKey Initiative:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Increase legal protection for the banking industry by establishing Perbanas Legal Working Commission and synergize with BI initiatives.</li>\r\n	<li>Legal advocacy for members.</li>\r\n	<li>Expert witness if needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide database related to antifraud matters.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div id="governance-division" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>8. Governance Division</h3>\r\nKey Initiatives:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Socialization on GCG in cooperation with KNKG or BI (3 x a year).</li>\r\n	<li>Socialization on ASEAN Score Card in cooperation with a third party (1 x a year).</li>\r\n	<li>Determine a standard GCG format specifically for Medium-Small Banks.</li>\r\n	<li>Finalization of GCG Guidelines in the Banking Sector.</li>\r\n	<li>Bank Indonesia version of GCG Score procedure.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div id="tech-division" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>9. Technology Division</h3>\r\nKey Initiatives:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Formulate a database for the Indonesian banking industry.</li>\r\n	<li>Architecture of Financial Services Transaction System and National Payment System.</li>\r\n	<li>Availability of reliable human resources and technology system.</li>\r\n	<li>Preparation on the establishment of consumer information bureau / Credit Information Management Institution (LPIP).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div id="pr-division" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>10. Public Relations Division</h3>\r\nKey Initiatives:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Maintain the image and existence of Perbanas as an organization and become a reliable partner to stakeholders.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide reliable banking information to all stakeholders.</li>\r\n	<li>Effective and informative media communication programs through Perbanas spokes-person, provide key messages, cooperate with the media, website, and other social information tools.</li>\r\n	<li>A sustainable banking education program through cooperation with BI and the Indonesian Financial Services Authority.</li>\r\n	<li>Banking CSR programs with a focus on education and community empowerment.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div id="sharia-banking-compartment" class="anchor-hww"></div>\r\n<h3>11. Sharia Banking Compartment</h3>\r\nKey Initiatives:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Product Manager Forum.</li>\r\n	<li>Syariah Goes to Campus.</li>\r\n	<li>Syariah Award.</li>\r\n	<li>Syariah Banking IB Net.</li>\r\n	<li>Syariah Banker Certification.</li>\r\n	<li>IBEX Participation.</li>\r\n	<li>Legal Studies on Syariah Banking.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;', 'How We Work', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-we-work', '', '', '2014-12-04 11:43:28', '2014-12-04 04:43:28', '', 0, 'http://perbanas.org/?page_id=419', 0, 'page', '', 0),
