(469, 1, '2014-06-12 11:50:46', '2014-06-12 04:50:46', 'Jakarta-General Meeting Extraordinary Shareholders (EGM) of Bank Mutiara, Jakarta, Monday, December 23, 2013, finally decided to increase the capital of Rp1, 249 trillion, so the CAR (capital adequacy ratio) The bank reached 14%. The position of the CAR in accordance with the ICAAP (Internal Capital Adequacy Assessment Proces / ICAAP).<!--more-->\r\n\r\nBanking community appreciated the steps LPS (Deposit Insurance Agency) as the bank\'s shareholders that the banking industry could grow healthy. Step LPS capital increase is also appropriate authority and the provisions of the Banking Law and the Law of LPS. Until the end of 2013, the bank\'s assets estimated at more than Rp15 trillion.\r\n\r\nChairman of the National Commercial Bank (PERBANAS), Sigit Pramono, decision support LPS bank\'s capital increase. "We will only discuss if LPS do otherwise. We must understand that in the case of Bank Mutiara, LPS position is as a shareholder of a bank that was saved. Not as a regulator. So, if the bank\'s indeed require additional capital that can be accounted for reasons and purposes, the LPS should approve it, "he said, in Jakarta, Monday, December 23, 2013.\r\n\r\nMoreover, they said Sigit, the law insists that LPS is responsible for the survival of a bank that was taken over to be resold pursuant. Meanwhile, according to some analysts, after the capital injection, the bank\'s financial performance will be improved and will ultimately increase the selling price. (Infobanknews.com)', 'Bankers Support Step LPS "Save" Bank Mutiara', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '459-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-12 11:50:46', '2014-06-12 04:50:46', '', 459, 'http://perbanas.org/en/459-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
